<HEADLINE> Peruvian Mining Exports Surpass $2.13 Billion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Peruvian main mining free on
board (FOB) exports reached 2.13 billion dollars during the
January-October period, the Energy and Mines Ministry said
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Gold,the most outstanding Peruvian mining export which ranks t
he first place together with copper, increased by 55.6 percent
the total value of its sales abroad.
</P>
<P>
Peru sold a total of 641.6 million dollars of gold during the
first 10 months of the year,compared with 412.2 million dollars
in the same period of 1997.
</P>
<P>
Copper remained with 641.8 million dollars, followed by zinc
with 366.4 million, lead with 162.2 million, refined silver with
196.5 million, tin with 102.3 million and iron with 80.5 million
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Energy and Mines Ministry spokesman said that 50 percent of
the country's hard currency are from the mining industry. 
</P>
